<img src=http://members.optushome.com.au/ahonnibal/smolderthumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Momz always said........if ya cant say nuttin nice....</span><hr size=1> Ashes,<br>
<br>
Now, you say you didn't actually -have- the cash ready when you made this deal with Thieven. Put yourself in her position. Seriously, how many people have you made a deal with, only to have them fall through? Countless times it's happened to me that someone says &quot;oh hold that for me, I'll have to sell some stuff to get the cash&quot;. Then you never fvcking hear from them again. Even if they arrange a time to be there, you got no guarantee that they're gonna be able to do the trade on time.<br>
<br>
Now if you were in Thieven's position, and you were waiting on someone purchasing something, what would you do if someone was willing to pay more, and had the cash right there? There's an old saying &quot;a bird in hand is better than two in the bush&quot;.<br>
<br>
Do you think she really cares if you consider her scum for falling through on a trade? Not likely.<br>
<br>
Also, consider this kind of situation if it happened in real life? A loose verbal agreement to do some trade. Wow, not very binding. If that kind of thing fell through, would you be upset? Maybe you would be, but would you be able to do anything about it? No way in hell.<br>
<br>
I think the reason you're upset about this is that you were getting a crazy good deal for the CBoL, and now that has been denied to you. Just buy a substitute weapon for now and keep looking for another one. Or here's an idea: Level some and maybe you can actually kill Wuoshi and get one the old fashioned way. <br>
<br>
Those 3 hours spent in EC tunnel could have been spent levelling towards a CBoL. <p>Trindade<br>
60th level warrior<br>
